{
 "cells": [
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "9bf046dc",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "# Usar Jupyter en Odoo.\n",
    "\n",
    "Para probar métodos del ORM y otras cosas en Odoo, podemos ejecutar la terminal de Odoo con [“odoo-binshell”](https://www.odoo.com/documentation/16.0/developer/reference/cli.html#shell) en la línea de comandos.\n",
    "\n",
    "No obstante eso puede ser un poco incómodo si queremos hacer pruebas más complejas, documentar o acceder desde otro host. \n",
    "\n",
    "Jupyter es un entorno de programación y documentación integrado. Produce una página web donde se puede programar en Python de forma interactiva y ver el resultado. \n",
    "\n",
    "Veremos cómo probar Odoo dentro de Jupyter para hacer tutoriales o usarlo en clase. \n",
    "\n",
    "<div class=\"alert alert-block alert-info\">\n",
    "    Lo que podremos hacer estará limitado por la propia librería odooRPC o por XML-RPC.\n",
    "</div>\n",
    "\n",
    "Odoo cuando arranca establece un entorno muy complejo. Jupyter en principio sólo está preparado para ejecutar Python “vanilla” e ir incorporando librerías. \n",
    "\n",
    "Una forma cómoda de instalar Jupyter y usarlo después es instalar Anaconda. En el caso de Linux, hay que seguir los pasos de la web y luego ejecutar anaconda-navigator en la terminal. \n",
    "En caso de no querer Anaconda, podemos ejecutar:\n",
    "```\n",
    "sudo pip install notebook\n",
    "jupyter notebook\n",
    "\n",
    "```\n",
    "\n",
    "## Con OdooRPC \n",
    "\n",
    "Para conectar el entorno de ejecución de Jupyter con Odoo, podemos usar su RPC. Hay una librería de la Odoo Community Association llamada OdooRPC [Documentación](https://pythonhosted.org/OdooRPC/) [Código](https://github.com/OCA/odoorpc) que facilita el uso del RPC de Odoo.\n",
    "\n",
    "Para instalarla: \n",
    "```\n",
    "pip install odoorpc \n",
    "```\n",
    "\n",
    "Esta librería es externa al proyecto Odoo y simplifica la conexión por XML-RPC, la cual explicaremos más adelante por si se queda corta esta librería.\n",
    "\n",
    "Veamos los diferentes comandos"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 1,
   "id": "c014b175",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "import odoorpc"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "975b0ecc",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "Después de importar la librería, nos conectamos al servidor que corresponda:\n",
    "\n",
    "<div class=\"alert alert-block alert-info\">\n",
    "  Por supuesto, las IP, usuarios, contraseñas y bases de datos hay que adaptarlos a los que tenga cada uno.\n",
    "</div>\n"
   ]
  },
  {

   "id": "c60ba65b",

   "source": [
    "## Con XML-RPC\n",
    "\n",
    "XML-RPC es un protocolo de llamada a procedimiento remoto (RPC, remote procedure call) que usa XML para codificar los datos y HTTP como protocolo de transmisión de mensajes.\n",
    "\n",
    "Si queremos acceder directamente a Odoo por su API, debemos conectarnos por [XML-RPC](https://www.odoo.com/documentation/16.0/developer/reference/external_api.html). Eso es lo que hace la librería explicada anteriormente. Haciéndolo directamente tenemos más opciones. Veamos cómo conectar:"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 17,
   "id": "dd98ef94",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [
    {
     "data": {
      "text/plain": [
       "{'server_version': '16.0-20230925',\n",
       " 'server_version_info': [16, 0, 0, 'final', 0, ''],\n",
       " 'server_serie': '16.0',\n",
       " 'protocol_version': 1}"
      ]
     },
     "execution_count": 17,
     "metadata": {},
     "output_type": "execute_result"
    }
   ],
   "source": [
    "import xmlrpc.client\n",
    "\n",
    "url = 'http://localhost:8069'\n",
    "db = 'demo'\n",
    "username = 'admin'\n",
    "password = 'Passw0rd'\n",
    "# El password puede ser una API Key generada desde el propio odoo\n",
    "\n",
    "common = xmlrpc.client.ServerProxy('{}/xmlrpc/2/common'.format(url))\n",
    "common.version()\n"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 18,
   "id": "44b0a684",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [
    {
     "name": "stdout",
     "output_type": "stream",
     "text": [
      "2\n"
     ]
    }
   ],
   "source": [
    "# Autenticar la conexión\n",
    "uid = common.authenticate(db, username, password, {})\n",
    "print(uid)"
   ]
  },

   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "67654863",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "Para hacer peticiones, debemos ejecutar la función RPC `execute_kw`.\n"

   "source": [
    "models = xmlrpc.client.ServerProxy('{}/xmlrpc/2/object'.format(url))\n",
    "# Consulta de los derechos de acceso. \n",

  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "fa82dded",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## Con JSON-RPC:\n",
    "\n",
    "Odoo también permite acceder directamente con [JSON-RPC](https://www.odoo.com/documentation/16.0/developer/howtos/web_services.html#json-rpc-library), similar al protocolo anterior\n"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 26,
   "id": "da5c4c3b",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [
    {
     "name": "stdout",
     "output_type": "stream",
     "text": [
      "b'{\"jsonrpc\": \"2.0\", \"method\": \"call\", \"params\": {\"service\": \"common\", \"method\": \"login\", \"args\": [\"demo\", \"admin\", \"Passw0rd\"]}, \"id\": 266197968}'\n",
      "b'{\"jsonrpc\": \"2.0\", \"method\": \"call\", \"params\": {\"service\": \"object\", \"method\": \"execute\", \"args\": [\"demo\", 2, \"Passw0rd\", \"res.partner\", \"search\", []]}, \"id\": 920304798}'\n",
      "[14, 26, 33, 27, 10, 35, 18, 19, 41, 11, 20, 22, 31, 23, 15, 34, 42, 43, 1, 39, 40, 12, 21, 25, 37, 24, 36, 30, 38, 13, 29, 28, 9, 17, 32, 16, 8, 3, 7]\n"
     ]
    }
   ],
   "source": [
    "import json\n",
    "import random\n",
    "import urllib.request\n",
    "\n",
    "HOST = 'localhost'\n",
    "PORT = 8069\n",
    "DB = 'demo'\n",
    "USER = 'admin'\n",
    "PASS = 'Passw0rd'\n",
    "\n",
    "def json_rpc(url, method, params):\n",
    "    data = {\n",
    "        \"jsonrpc\": \"2.0\",\n",
    "        \"method\": method,\n",
    "        \"params\": params,\n",
    "        \"id\": random.randint(0, 1000000000),\n",
    "    }\n",
    "    print(json.dumps(data).encode())\n",
    "    req = urllib.request.Request(url=url, data=json.dumps(data).encode(), headers={\n",
    "        \"Content-Type\":\"application/json\",\n",
    "    })\n",
    "    reply = json.loads(urllib.request.urlopen(req).read().decode('UTF-8'))\n",
    "    if reply.get(\"error\"):\n",
    "        raise Exception(reply[\"error\"])\n",
    "    return reply[\"result\"]\n",
    "\n",
    "def call(url, service, method, *args):\n",
    "    return json_rpc(url, \"call\", {\"service\": service, \"method\": method, \"args\": args})\n",
    "\n",
    "# log in the given database\n",
    "url = \"http://%s:%s/jsonrpc\" % (HOST, PORT)\n",
    "uid = call(url, \"common\", \"login\", DB, USER, PASS)\n",
    "\n",
    "# create a new note\n",
    "args = []\n",
    "clients = call(url, \"object\", \"execute\", DB, uid, PASS, 'res.partner', 'search', args)\n",
    "print(clients)"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "63f86aa3",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "Si observamos lo que envía al servidor, es un JSON en un determinado formato. Informa del método \"call\" y los parámetros como indica el estándar JSON-RPC https://www.jsonrpc.org/specification.\n",
    "\n",
    "A continuación, en los \"params\" es donde hay que especificar la petición RPC a Odoo. En el primer ejemplo lo envía al \"service\" \"common\" para hacer \"login\" y les envía los argumentos que el login necesita. \n",
    "\n",
    "Aquí podemos encontrar información, aunque sea de XML-RPC: https://www.odoo.com/documentation/14.0/developer/reference/external_api.html \n",
    "\n",
    "Después, en el \"service\" \"object\" le pedimos que ejecute un método del ORM. En este caso es el método \"search\". El resto de argumentos lo pasamos en un array, ya que los necesita de forma posicional. \n",
    "\n",
    "### Read\n",
    "\n",
    "En el siguiente ejemplo hacemos lo mismo, pero con el método \"read\", pero vemos que los argumentos los pasa en el mismo órden que el search anterior: base de datos, uid, password, modelo, método ORM, argumentos, en este caso necesita dos argumentos, un array de ids y los fields que va a tener que leer. "
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 27,
   "id": "76ab5e58",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [
    {
     "name": "stdout",
     "output_type": "stream",
     "text": [
      "b'{\"jsonrpc\": \"2.0\", \"method\": \"call\", \"params\": {\"service\": \"object\", \"method\": \"execute\", \"args\": [\"demo\", 2, \"Passw0rd\", \"res.partner\", \"read\", [14, 26], [\"name\", \"country_id\", \"comment\"]]}, \"id\": 282424954}'\n",
      "[{'id': 14, 'name': 'Azure Interior', 'country_id': [233, 'United States'], 'comment': False}, {'id': 26, 'name': 'Brandon Freeman', 'country_id': [233, 'United States'], 'comment': False}]\n"
     ]
    }
   ],
   "source": [
    "\n",
    "clients_data = call(url, \"object\", \"execute\", DB, uid, PASS, 'res.partner', 'read', [14,26],['name', 'country_id', 'comment'])\n",
    "print(clients_data)"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "d93f5d49",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "Veamos ahora un ejemplo para cada función típica del ORM de Odoo:"

  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "9ca7c593",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "### Write\n",
    "Para actualizar un registro"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 31,
   "id": "f4679257",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [
    {
     "name": "stdout",

    "clients_fields = call(url, \"object\", \"execute\", DB, uid, PASS, 'res.partner', 'fields_get', ['name'])\n",
    "print(clients_fields)"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 31,
   "id": "7bab5b53",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [
    {
     "name": "stdout",

     "text": [
      "b'{\"jsonrpc\": \"2.0\", \"method\": \"call\", \"params\": {\"service\": \"object\", \"method\": \"execute\", \"args\": [\"roma\", 2, \"1234\", \"res.partner\", \"fields_get\", [\"name\"], [\"string\", \"type\"]]}, \"id\": 741552539}'\n",
      "{'name': {'string': 'Name', 'type': 'char'}}\n"
     ]
    }

    "clients_fields = call(url, \"object\", \"execute\", DB, uid, PASS, 'res.partner', 'fields_get', ['name'], ['string', 'type'])\n",
    "print(clients_fields)"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "8ce7977a",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    " ## Autenticación con Odoo y JSON-RPC\n",
    " \n",
    " Supongamos que queremos hacer una aplicación para consultar datos de Odoo o usarlo como método de autenticación de usuarios.\n",
    " Los usuarios están en res.users y Odoo ya tiene su sistema de autenticación en el \"Service\" \"Common\". Este no es necesario siempre, ya que cualquier petición es \"stateless\" y necesita que enviemos el usuario y contraseña. Pero hace falta para saber el \"uid\" del usuario que va a hacer la petición."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 23,
   "id": "1ed47c77",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [
    {
     "name": "stdout",
     "output_type": "stream",
     "text": [
      "b'{\"jsonrpc\": \"2.0\", \"method\": \"call\", \"params\": {\"service\": \"common\", \"method\": \"login\", \"args\": [\"roma\", \"admin\", \"1234\"]}, \"id\": 754521245}'\n",
      "User: 2\n"
     ]
    }
   ],
   "source": [
    "uid = call(url, \"common\", \"login\", DB, USER, PASS)\n",
    "print(\"User:\", uid)"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "b4852c76",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "### Crear usuarios\n",
    "Puede que necesitemos crear usuarios desde una aplicación externa. "
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 25,
   "id": "231a7546",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [
    {
     "name": "stdout",
     "output_type": "stream",
     "text": [
      "b'{\"jsonrpc\": \"2.0\", \"method\": \"call\", \"params\": {\"service\": \"object\", \"method\": \"execute\", \"args\": [\"roma\", 2, \"1234\", \"res.users\", \"create\", {\"name\": \"New User\", \"login\": \"new_user\", \"password\": \"1234\", \"email\": \"new@email.com\"}]}, \"id\": 595415685}'\n"
     ]
    }
   ],
   "source": [
    "new_user = call(url, \"object\", \"execute\", DB, uid, PASS, 'res.users', 'create', {\"name\": \"New User\", \"login\": \"new_user\", \"password\": \"1234\", \"email\": \"new@email.com\"})"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 26,
   "id": "620354fd",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [
    {
     "name": "stdout",
     "output_type": "stream",
     "text": [
      "35\n"
     ]
    }
   ],
   "source": [
    "print(new_user)"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "a523009d",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "Esto crea automáticamente un nuevo \"res.partner\" que podemos utilizar como cliente. Podemos saber el id del \"res.partner\" inspeccionando el field many2one que los relaciona:"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 31,
   "id": "ddd90cda",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [
    {
     "name": "stdout",
     "output_type": "stream",
     "text": [
      "b'{\"jsonrpc\": \"2.0\", \"method\": \"call\", \"params\": {\"service\": \"object\", \"method\": \"execute\", \"args\": [\"roma\", 2, \"1234\", \"res.users\", \"read\", [35], [\"login\", \"partner_id\"]]}, \"id\": 751902356}'\n",
      "[{'id': 35, 'login': 'new_user', 'partner_id': [71, 'New User']}]\n"
     ]
    }
   ],
   "source": [
    "user_data = call(url, \"object\", \"execute\", DB, uid, PASS, 'res.users', 'read', [new_user],['login', 'partner_id'])\n",
    "print(user_data)"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 32,
   "id": "66c9850f",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [
    {
     "name": "stdout",
     "output_type": "stream",
     "text": [
      "71\n"
     ]
    }
   ],
   "source": [
    "partner_id = user_data[0]['partner_id'][0]\n",
    "print(partner_id)"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "8ca31af2",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "Veamos cómo se puede hacer login con el nuevo usuario:"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 33,
   "id": "9f7abc6c",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [
    {
     "name": "stdout",
     "output_type": "stream",
     "text": [
      "b'{\"jsonrpc\": \"2.0\", \"method\": \"call\", \"params\": {\"service\": \"common\", \"method\": \"login\", \"args\": [\"roma\", \"new_user\", \"1234\"]}, \"id\": 671523811}'\n",
      "User: 35\n"
     ]
    }
   ],
   "source": [
    "uid_new_user = call(url, \"common\", \"login\", DB, 'new_user', '1234')\n",
    "print(\"User:\", uid_new_user)"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "67a5e8aa",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## Gestión de ventas con JSON-RPC\n",
    "En este caso vamos a implementar un proceso muy común. Supongamos que queremos crear una venta desde una aplicación externa. \n",
    "El modelos es \"sale.order\" y cada línea es \"sale.order.line\". Por otro lado, los productos a vender están en \"product.product\". \n",
    "Lo primero que haremos será listar los productos, mostraremos los primeros 5:"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 77,
   "id": "4cb48912",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [
    {
     "name": "stdout",
     "output_type": "stream",
     "text": [
      "b'{\"jsonrpc\": \"2.0\", \"method\": \"call\", \"params\": {\"service\": \"object\", \"method\": \"execute\", \"args\": [\"roma\", 2, \"1234\", \"product.product\", \"search_read\", [], [\"name\"], 0, 5]}, \"id\": 15104186}'\n",
      "[{'id': 36, 'name': 'Customizable Desk'}, {'id': 37, 'name': 'Customizable Desk'}, {'id': 16, 'name': 'Corner Desk Right Sit'}, {'id': 17, 'name': 'Large Cabinet'}, {'id': 18, 'name': 'Storage Box'}]\n"
     ]
    }
   ],
   "source": [
    "products = call(url, \"object\", \"execute\", DB, uid, PASS, 'product.product', 'search_read', [],['name'], 0, 5)\n",
    "print(products)"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "11962613",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "Imaginemos que el cliente elige el 1er producto:"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 78,
   "id": "6e04bf85",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [
    {
     "name": "stdout",
     "output_type": "stream",
     "text": [
      "Product: 36\n"
     ]
    }
   ],
   "source": [
    "product = products[0]['id']\n",
    "print(\"Product:\",product)"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "6ea1b7e6",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "Suponiendo que el cliente es el creado anteriormente, vamos a hacer una venta:"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 79,
   "id": "3734f6c5",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [
    {
     "name": "stdout",
     "output_type": "stream",
     "text": [
      "b'{\"jsonrpc\": \"2.0\", \"method\": \"call\", \"params\": {\"service\": \"object\", \"method\": \"execute\", \"args\": [\"roma\", 2, \"1234\", \"sale.order\", \"create\", {\"partner_id\": 35}]}, \"id\": 838607333}'\n",
      "Sale Order 37\n"
     ]
    }
   ],
   "source": [
    "sale = call(url, \"object\", \"execute\", DB, uid, PASS, 'sale.order', 'create', {\"partner_id\": new_user})\n",
    "print(\"Sale Order\", sale)"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 80,
   "id": "1deec55b",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [
    {
     "name": "stdout",
     "output_type": "stream",
     "text": [
      "b'{\"jsonrpc\": \"2.0\", \"method\": \"call\", \"params\": {\"service\": \"object\", \"method\": \"execute\", \"args\": [\"roma\", 2, \"1234\", \"sale.order.line\", \"create\", {\"order_id\": 37, \"product_id\": 36, \"product_uom_qty\": 3}]}, \"id\": 478261323}'\n",
      "72\n"
     ]
    }
   ],
   "source": [
    "sale_line = call(url, \"object\", \"execute\", DB, uid, PASS, 'sale.order.line', 'create', {\n",
    "    \"order_id\": sale, \n",
    "    \"product_id\": product,\n",
    "    \"product_uom_qty\": 3\n",
    "})\n",
    "print(sale_line)"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "07d6d4b6",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "Cuando se hace un pedido en Odoo, este tiene diversos estados: Presupuesto, Pedido, Pedido pagado/entregado.., Factura, Factura Pagada. \n",
    "De momento hemos creado un presupuesto. Vamos a crear la factura y a suponer que se ha pagado. El proceso intermedio lo podría estar haciendo la aplicación externa.\n",
    "El que un presupuesto pase a pedido no es tan sólo cambiar su campo \"state\". El modelo \"sale.order\" tiene un método específico \"action_confirm\""
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 81,
   "id": "7f4dec30",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [
    {
     "name": "stdout",
     "output_type": "stream",
     "text": [
      "b'{\"jsonrpc\": \"2.0\", \"method\": \"call\", \"params\": {\"service\": \"object\", \"method\": \"execute\", \"args\": [\"roma\", 2, \"1234\", \"sale.order\", \"action_confirm\", [37]]}, \"id\": 81084096}'\n"
     ]
    },
    {
     "data": {
      "text/plain": [
       "True"
      ]
     },
     "execution_count": 81,
     "metadata": {},
     "output_type": "execute_result"
    }
   ],
   "source": [
    "call(url, \"object\", \"execute\", DB, uid, PASS, 'sale.order', 'action_confirm', [sale])"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "09829bd9",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "Ahora queremos hacer la factura, pero antes hay que indicar que está todo entregado:"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 82,
   "id": "adec2539",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [
    {
     "name": "stdout",
     "output_type": "stream",
     "text": [
      "b'{\"jsonrpc\": \"2.0\", \"method\": \"call\", \"params\": {\"service\": \"object\", \"method\": \"execute\", \"args\": [\"roma\", 2, \"1234\", \"sale.order\", \"read\", [37], [\"order_line\"]]}, \"id\": 512544583}'\n",
      "[72]\n"
     ]
    }
   ],
   "source": [
    "sale_lines =  call(url, \"object\", \"execute\", DB, uid, PASS, 'sale.order', 'read', [sale],['order_line'])[0]['order_line']\n",
    "print(sale_lines)"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 83,
   "id": "4b37b30f",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [
    {
     "name": "stdout",
     "output_type": "stream",
     "text": [
      "b'{\"jsonrpc\": \"2.0\", \"method\": \"call\", \"params\": {\"service\": \"object\", \"method\": \"execute\", \"args\": [\"roma\", 2, \"1234\", \"sale.order.line\", \"read\", [72], [\"product_uom_qty\"]]}, \"id\": 815155193}'\n",
      "[{'id': 72, 'product_uom_qty': 3.0}]\n"
     ]
    }
   ],
   "source": [
    "quantities = call(url, \"object\", \"execute\", DB, uid, PASS, 'sale.order.line', 'read', sale_lines,['product_uom_qty'])\n",
    "print(quantities)"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 84,
   "id": "daf09207",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [
    {
     "name": "stdout",
     "output_type": "stream",
     "text": [
      "b'{\"jsonrpc\": \"2.0\", \"method\": \"call\", \"params\": {\"service\": \"object\", \"method\": \"execute\", \"args\": [\"roma\", 2, \"1234\", \"sale.order.line\", \"write\", 72, {\"qty_delivered\": 3.0}]}, \"id\": 461566654}'\n"
     ]
    }
   ],
   "source": [
    "for s in quantities:\n",
    "    call(url, \"object\", \"execute\", DB, uid, PASS, 'sale.order.line', 'write', s['id'], {\"qty_delivered\": s['product_uom_qty']})"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "fab7bb96",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "Crear una factura a partir de un \"sale.order\" no es una tarea sencilla. Odoo proporciona un Wizard con varias opciones y con todo eso llama a una función. La función está implementada en propio wizard y es muy compleja (https://github.com/odoo/odoo/blob/17.0/addons/sale/wizard/sale_make_invoice_advance.py#L195)\n",
    "Por ello, lo más cómodo puede ser crear un wizard (el transient model) y luego llamar a la función"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 85,
   "id": "61f5c306",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [
    {
     "name": "stdout",
     "output_type": "stream",
     "text": [
      "b'{\"jsonrpc\": \"2.0\", \"method\": \"call\", \"params\": {\"service\": \"object\", \"method\": \"execute\", \"args\": [\"roma\", 2, \"1234\", \"sale.advance.payment.inv\", \"create\", {\"sale_order_ids\": [37]}]}, \"id\": 447156165}'\n",
      "7\n"
     ]
    }
   ],
   "source": [
    "invoice_wizard = call(url, \"object\", \"execute\", DB, uid, PASS, 'sale.advance.payment.inv', 'create', \n",
    "                      {\"sale_order_ids\": [sale]}\n",
    "                     )\n",
    "print(invoice_wizard)"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 86,
   "id": "d775470d",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [
    {
     "name": "stdout",
     "output_type": "stream",
     "text": [
      "b'{\"jsonrpc\": \"2.0\", \"method\": \"call\", \"params\": {\"service\": \"object\", \"method\": \"execute\", \"args\": [\"roma\", 2, \"1234\", \"sale.advance.payment.inv\", \"create_invoices\", [7]]}, \"id\": 726235557}'\n"
     ]
    }
   ],
   "source": [
    "invoice = call(url, \"object\", \"execute\", DB, uid, PASS, 'sale.advance.payment.inv', 'create_invoices', [invoice_wizard])"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 87,
   "id": "264355e1",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [
    {
     "name": "stdout",
     "output_type": "stream",
     "text": [
      "{'type': 'ir.actions.act_window_close'}\n"
     ]
    }
   ],
   "source": [
    "print(invoice)"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "2ac56c06",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "Como se puede ver, la factura creada no es retornada por la función, pero la podemos consultar de nuevo desde sale.order:\n"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 88,
   "id": "6cf3d09f",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [
    {
     "name": "stdout",
     "output_type": "stream",
     "text": [
      "b'{\"jsonrpc\": \"2.0\", \"method\": \"call\", \"params\": {\"service\": \"object\", \"method\": \"execute\", \"args\": [\"roma\", 2, \"1234\", \"sale.order\", \"read\", [37], [\"invoice_ids\"]]}, \"id\": 859188960}'\n",
      "37\n"
     ]
    }
   ],
   "source": [
    "invoice =  call(url, \"object\", \"execute\", DB, uid, PASS, 'sale.order', 'read', [sale],['invoice_ids'])[0]['invoice_ids'][0]\n",
    "print(invoice)"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "360d072d",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "Ahora hay que confirmar la factura:"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 89,
   "id": "66d3ebad",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [
    {
     "name": "stdout",
     "output_type": "stream",
     "text": [
      "b'{\"jsonrpc\": \"2.0\", \"method\": \"call\", \"params\": {\"service\": \"object\", \"method\": \"execute\", \"args\": [\"roma\", 2, \"1234\", \"account.move\", \"action_post\", [37]]}, \"id\": 441705469}'\n"
     ]
    },
    {
     "data": {
      "text/plain": [
       "False"
      ]
     },
     "execution_count": 89,
     "metadata": {},
     "output_type": "execute_result"
    }
   ],
   "source": [
    "call(url, \"object\", \"execute\", DB, uid, PASS, 'account.move', 'action_post', [invoice])"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "acde04aa",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "Ahora habría que registrar el pago, lo cual es similar a crear la factura, ya que Odoo lo hace con un wizard. "
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "8a547c9f",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "Una vez hecha la factura hay que descargarla en PDF. Odoo utiliza un software externo llamado Wkhtmltopdf que debería estar instalado en el sistema. En caso de querer una vista prévia en HTML, podemos ir a la URL que también proporciona Odoo, en este caso: http://localhost:8069/report/html/account.report_invoice/36 siendo 36 el id de la invoice creada. En esta url tenemos la versión pdf si está instalado Wkhtmltopdf: http://localhost:8069/report/pdf/account.report_invoice/36"
   ]
  },
